A man, believed to be in his 30s, was killed Friday morning when his vehicle collided head-on with a truck on the Klerkskraal Road in Carletonville, ER24 said in a statement. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said on arrival, paramedics found the truck and wrecked car lying on opposite sides of the road. Paramedics inspected the scene and found the driver of the car lying trapped and motionless inside his vehicle. Unfortunately, the man had already succumbed to his multiple, fatal injuries. Nothing could be done for the man, and he was declared dead on the scene. ALSO READ: Details of West Rand home invasion emerge The driver of the truck escaped injury. The cause of the collision was not yet known, but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. [CARLETONVILLE] &#8211; Man killed when car and truck collide head-on. https://t.co/OdzFeJVbe7 @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews @_ArriveAlive &mdash; ER24 EMS (Pty) Ltd. (@ER24EMS) February 3, 2017 African News Agency (ANA)